It's sad Marvel couldn't stay true to that comics due to character and plot constraints brought about them not owning all of their characters. They had to use Bucky here where he shouldn't have been. The real reason behind it is more political.  Due to the increasing numbers of B-list heroes who have been blatantly failing in saving people, the government issued a mandate that all past, present and future "inhumans/Enhanceds" must be registered and be screened fit to to be a hero with it they also have to surrender their secret identities. Capt. America saw this as a liability rather than a fix. What if the enemy managed to hack said registry and used all that info against the heroes. He opposed the mandate backed up by the Avengers and affiliated heroes

Iron Man and Ant-man saw this a sign of stability. They were tired of B-list heroes left unchecked who more bad than good and they also saw earth-foreign entities as a liability and could not be fully trusted.  What they wanted was a sense of order that could help everyday citizens rather than wannabe heroes running amok.


All in all, Cant wait for this! whoo!
